</div></div><div class="lb-region lb-region--right"><div class="block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockrecommended-stories-mini"><h2>Recommended Stories</h2><div class="teaser-column"><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/surge-violence-fuels-humanitarian-crisis-haiti" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2024-02/UNI516128%20Haiti%20banner.jpg?itok=7rRTknGk" width="458" height="305" alt="Seven-year-old Lovenska of Haiti works on a drawing at a UNICEF-supported child-friendly space in Delmas 6, downtown Port-au-Prince." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Surge in Violence Fuels <strong>Humanitarian Crisis in Haiti</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Calling the situation for children "a living nightmare," UNICEF Haiti Representative Bruno Maes urges more support for the emergency response. [VIDEO]</p></div></a></div></article><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/rising-malnutrition-puts-childrens-lives-grave-risk-gaza" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2024-02/UNI519938.jpg?itok=Px5meLsZ" width="458" height="305" alt="In the Gaza Strip on Feb. 15, 2024, a UNICEF-trained screener measures 2-year-old Leen&#039;s mid-upper arm circumference to diagnose severe acute malnutrition." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Rising Malnutrition Puts <strong>Children&#039;s Lives at Grave Risk in Gaza</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>An unprecedentedly rapid rise in malnutrition is threatening the lives of children and pregnant and breastfeeding women in the Gaza Strip.</p></div></a></div></article><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/children-war-write-poems-peace" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2024-02/Muzdalifa%20poem%20for%20peace.jpg?itok=Xj4Z4GuY" width="458" height="339" alt="Muzdalifa, 17, of Sudan, wrote a poem for peace expressing her hope for the future." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Children in War Write <strong>Poems for Peace</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>UNICEF shares its growing collection of poems by young people — deeply personal works that show resilience, creativity and hope in the face of danger.</p></div></a></div></article></div></div></div></div> </section>
